Service Cloud
What’s Service?
Set Up Email-to-Case with a Guided Setup Flow

Get your cases into Service Cloud fast with a quick guided setup flow for Email-to-Case. Connect your support email address to Salesforce, give your incoming cases a default priority and queue, and set up mail forwarding so your emails become cases for your support team.

Service Setup is available in Lightning Experience
Available in: All editions with the Service Cloud

Click the gear icon and select Service Setup.
Connect your support email address to Salesforce and turn on the on-demand email service
Specify a queue and priority for the cases that are created from your email
Verify your email address with Salesforce
Set up email forwarding from your email service provider to Service Cloud

After completing the flow, check your settings on the Email-to-Case page in Setup. For example, you may want to deselect the option to create tasks for case owners when an email is converted to a case.

(Optional) Set up an Omni-Channel flow to route cases to the right queues or agents.
(Optional) To help agents search email message records easily, add the EmailMessage object to your agents’ profiles.
title: Setting Up Email-to-Case in Salesforce
